<br>
It has a lot of features for users that Ezboard doesn't.  The features I particularily like, and would probably be extremely handy for this message forum are:<br>
<br>
Users can turn on/off having to look at other people's signatures.  God, to not have to look at some of those massive graphics that take up more room than the posts, would be sweet.<br>
<br>
You can also set up an ignore list.  Whoa!  Seems like that'd have powerful potential to screen out the twerps clammoring for attention by bumping old threads or spamming the forums.<br>
<br>
Administrators can setup their own rules for signatures and it automatically enforces them.   Not sure what other administrator goodies there are.  Speed seems very good.  Much better than the UBB board the clerics used to have.<br>
<br>
Both the eqclerics and eqshamans site are using this message forum.  I'm sure there's probably people, like myself, that would pony up some money to purchase the software should someone have a system to host it on. <br>
<br>
Anyway, just a suggestion and worth every penny you paid for it.<br>
