<br>
EZboard is used because the costs involved in hosting a busy message board become tremendous in very short order - boards are too CPU intensive for shared servers at normal web hosts, even with premium unlimited bandwidth accounts.<br>
<br>
I was hosting TK's boards for many years, but even our fairly small guild ended up ganking the CPU processes at my host and we were forced to move to EZboard.<br>
<br>
Compare, for our guild, EZboard charges around $120 per 6 months of Gold.  My host (which is one of the better ones I've had) is $240 per year for the shared hosting plan I was on, which our board was stressing to the point that they were going to cancel me as a customer if I didn't reduce the load, or move to a dedicated server.<br>
<br>
A 'cheap' dedicated server is $100 / month at least.<br>
<br>
If you are running a message board that EZboard charges between $100 and $1200 per year for Gold, EZboard is a good deal.<br>
<br>
If you are running a message board that EZboard wants $1500+ for, then it might be time to look at dedicated hosting on some other software.<br>
